  m_Name: CornflowerInfo
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::PlantInfoData
  plantName: Cornflower
  description: "The cornflower (Centaurea cyanus) is a vibrant blue wildflower, often
    called a bachelor\u2019s button, blue bottle, or bluet. It symbolizes hope, delicacy,
    refinement, and, in folklore, love and fidelity. It is commonly used in skincare
    for its anti-inflammatory properties, as a culinary garnish, and as a popular
    choice for wedding bouquets."
